cal architecture-all difficulties that have contributed incrementally to Ukrainian citizens' anger against their government. This thoroughly revised edition brings Cybriwsky's account of events and their ramifications fully up to date, offering the clearest picture we've had yet of what has happened-and what is likely still to come-in Ukraine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aKyiv, postsocialist cities, urban development, urban societies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311070065740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048531738zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048531738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048531738.jpg  a978-3-11-060651-5  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-070065-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK